News Corp. net profit falls 1.7 percent in first half 
Global media conglomerate News Corp. said Thursday its net profit after
abnormals fell 1.7 percent from a year earlier to 690 million
Australian dollars (527.9 million US) in the six months to December.
The result was after abnormal losses of 41 million Australian dollars,
compared with abnormal gains of 39 million dollars in the same period a
year before.
News said sales rose 4.7 percent to 7.1 billion Australian dollars in
the period.
The company has been forecasting 20 percent growth in profits for the
full year to June.
